description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Registered Mental Health (RMN)/ Learning Disability Nurse (RNLD)&lt;/strong&gt; with a passion for delivering the best quality of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time role and you will be working 40 hours per week at Cygnet Pindar House.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Pindar House&lt;/strong&gt; is our new 22 bed Neuropsychiatric rehabilitation facility for men affected by acquired brain injuries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to enjoy excellent career prospects whilereaping the rewards of making a difference to others – every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for the co-ordination, assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of individual Patient programs of care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all Staff contributes to the efficient running of the Hospital and the creation of an atmosphere conducive to the best interests of the Patients – duties may include acting up for the Head of Care and/or the Hospital Manager in their absence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any ill health amongst Patients and make requests for R.M.O / GP / Professional visits where necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To support empowerment of Patients having regard for their dignity, rights and advice, whilst maintaining professional responsibility for individuals in our care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that individual care plans are completed and maintained in conjunction with Patient, Relatives and other Health Care Professionals, and in accordance with NMC guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To participate in the planning, delivery and evaluation of specific therapeutic interventions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess Patients in all aspects of their care needs to provide health supervision and attention through direct Nursing Care when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to date knowledge of legislation in relation to Learning Difficulties and/or Mental Health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are a Registered Mental Health/Learning Disability Nurse with a valid pin (at least 2 years’ experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to communicate at all levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to network, establish and maintain relationships with PCT’s/Healthcare Commission/Local Residents and representatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience in Acute, Rehabilitation, Mental Health, Learning Disabilities or forensic psychiatry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident and Assertive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Health Care&lt;/strong&gt; has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Pindar House&lt;/strong&gt; is our new 22 bed Neuropsychiatric rehabilitation facility for men affected by acquired brain injuries. It is a safe and secure place to aid recovery as well as offering those diagnosed with a progressive neurological disease, like Huntington’s disease, a caring and long term placement to support and help manage the progression of their symptoms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is a modern purpose built facility that has been designed specifically to provide a clinically led evidence based neuropsychiatric pathway for those individuals presenting with behaviours that challenge. Our focus is to create a therapeutic rich environment which engages our service users and offers them the opportunity to minimise their challenging behaviour and maximise their independence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you care about making a difference – we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click the link to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
